The paper deals with the design of subexponential parameterized algorithms on special classes of graphs, particularly map graphs. This involves the use of combinatorial and decomposition techniques, which are common in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the use of tree decompositions, which are a fundamental tool in algorithm design and analysis (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the improvement of existing algorithms for problems such as Feedback Vertex Set and Cycle Packing, which are classic problems in graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
